																		Merry 11 Days Before Christmas!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164945" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1450105342 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Dec 2015 15:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2423632">
									

<p>I was planning on holding off on this one a little longer, but I'm going to be out of town in the next few days and wanted to make sure I got it up when I needed to.</p>
<p>First, some credits. Obviously this tale is inspired <em>extremely</em> heavily by various scripts and adaptations of &quot;A Christmas Carol&quot; by Charles Dickens. If you haven't seen it yet, find a local theatre troupe and watch their performance of it (they're almost definitely performing it). It's one of my favorite plays, and I think you'll enjoy it too.</p>
<p>All images used (except the title bar) are from SunnyClockwork, and they are dope.</p>
<p>Edit: Also thanks to psul below for catching things I had missed, as well as noting a much needed improvement.</p>
<p>Lastly, thanks to everybody who had a glance at this in chat and approved (or otherwise). I know this isn't going to be for everyone, and I respect if you don't want to slog through the whole thing, but I really enjoyed writing it and I hope you enjoy reading it, too.</p>
<p>Merry (Early) Christmas!</p>

							</div>

								
